Movie theater shooting suspect James Holmes set up an elaborate booby trap system in his apartment, which included improvised napalm and thermite, to pull cops away from the massacre, it was claimed in court on Tuesday.

Holmes, who is accused of opening fire at moviegoers during a midnight screening of The Dark Knight Rises last July is charged with more than 160 counts, including murder and attempted murder.

The previously unheard details of Holmes' plot were laid out in court today during an ongoing hearing as prosecutors presented their case against the 25-year-old.

