While prosecutors have yet to decide on whether they will seek the death penalty, such a plea could get Holmes a lesser sentence, such as life in prison; help the state avoid a costly trial; and spare survivors and families of those who died from the trauma of going through a lengthy trial.

Yesterday, the first responders to arrive after Holmes waged the shooting rampage gave harrowing accounts of the massacre in court.

The first to speak was Officer Jason Oviatt from the Aurora, Colorado Police Department.

He was the one who ordered Holmes onto the ground and handcuffed him after he spotted the alleged shooter 'just standing there' in full swat gear.

